Taiwan Stocks: Macronix, Powertech, Tripod, TSMC, Unimicron

-- B y   W e i y i   L i m
-- 
2011-07-29T05:48:04Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-29/taiwan-stocks-macronix-powertech-tsmc-unimicron-technology.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in Taiwan trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the 1:30 p.m. close in Taipei.  The Taiex Index fell 123.02, or 1.4 percent, to 8,644.18.
The benchmark dropped 1.4 percent this week, wiping out its
gains for the month.  Macronix International (2337)  Co. (2337 TT), a maker of flash-
memory chips, sank 6.8 percent to NT$14.40, the lowest close
since June 30, 2009, after Macquarie Group Ltd. and KGI
Securities Co. cut their ratings on the company.  Nintendo Co., a client, slashed its profit forecast 82
percent to 20 billion yen after lower-than-expected sales of its
new 3-D handheld player led it to cut prices of the product.  Powertech Technology Inc. (6239)  (6239 TT) slumped 7 percent to
NT$82.90, the biggest drop since Dec. 3, 2008. The company’s
second-quarter profit was NT$1.87 billion ($65 million), less
than NT$2 billion in the same period a year earlier, according
to Bloomberg data.  Taiwan Semiconductor Manufacturing Co. (2330 TT) lost 1.4
percent to NT$72, the biggest loss since July 19. The world’s
largest contract manufacturer of chips said second-quarter net
income fell 11 percent to NT$36 billion. The average of 15
analyst estimates compiled by Bloomberg was for profit of
NT$36.4 billion.  Tripod Technology Corp. (3044)  (3044 TT), a printed circuit maker,
tumbled 6.9 percent to NT$114.50, the biggest retreat since Feb.
5, 2010, after Credit Suisse Group AG cut the company to
“neutral” from “outperform,” citing weakness in the chip,
notebook and flat panel industries.  Unimicron Technology Corp. (3037)  (3037 TT), a printed circuit
board maker, slid 5.9 percent to NT$51.30, the biggest drop
since March 15, after Yuanta Securities Co., HSBC Holding Co.
and Credit Suisse lowered their ratings on the shares.  To contact the reporter on this story:
